      "side": 1,
      "message": "My suggested alternative is to support blacklists based on IsAncestor. I think that would solve most blacklisting. Examples, where BL is the revision I\u0027m checking for blacklisting:\n- Blacklist Nexus6p where I haven\u0027t updated the build number: !IsAncestor(\"6ab223e0f0203225c9cf019b56561489027e4b0d\", BL)\n- Blacklist a range of CLs that are killing the bots: IsAncestor(\u003cbreak\u003e, BL) \u0026\u0026 !IsAncestor(\u003cfix\u003e, BL)\n- Blacklist skia-master, but not dev-branch: IsAncestor(BL, \"skia-master\") \u0026\u0026 !IsAncestor(BL, \"dev-branch\")\n\nMaking a UI that\u0027s intuitive is a bit more complicated...",
